   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter" part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_702_1843-03-30_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>March 30 <hi rend="superscript">th</hi>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Trim_IE" instant="false" full="yes">Trim</placeName>
                  <date when="1843-03-30" instant="false">March 30<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1843</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName instant="false" full="yes"/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p part="N">
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Trim_IE" instant="false" full="yes">Trim</placeName> - March 30 <hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1843
               <note anchored="true">68</note>
            </p>
            <p part="N"> 
               Your <hi rend="underline">lark</hi> sang delight<lb/>
               fully at its rising, and in<lb/>
               the whole of its flight &amp;<lb/>
               descent - How much<choice>
                  <orig>plea<lb/>
                     sure</orig>
                  <reg instant="false">pleasure</reg>
               </choice>
               you gave dearest <choice>
                  <orig>mo-<lb/>
                     ther</orig>
                  <reg instant="false">
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2" instant="false" full="yes">mother</persName>
                  </reg>
               </choice>
               you can hardly know<lb/>
               unless you could see &amp; hear<lb/>
               behind your back as well<lb/>
               as before your face -<lb/>
               I never was more delighted<lb/>
               than by the surprise of<lb/>
               seeing your dear rosy face<lb/>
               lightening upon me and so<lb/>
               affectionately &amp; unexpectedly<lb/>
               and I only wish I had that<lb/>
               hug over again -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
               We all, - meaning <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeH1" instant="false" full="yes">Harriet</persName>
               <lb/>
               &amp; myself<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_702_1843-03-30_page02.jpg"/>
      
               have agreed that under<lb/>
               your staid, prove, every <lb/>
               day demeanour and <lb/>
               matronly <del instant="false" status="unremarkable">habits</del> and<lb/>
               Grandmotherian habits<lb/>
               you have a <hi rend="underline">deal</hi> of romance<lb/>
               deep down that sprouts up<lb/>
               to day unexpectedly every<lb/>
               now and then - Kind <choice>
                  <orig>fa<lb/> 
                     ther</orig>
                  <reg instant="false">father</reg>
               </choice>
               ther for you - And God bless<lb/>
               you for it - and often may<lb/>
               it sprout for our delight<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">I hope dearest mother<lb/>
               that the pleasure you have<lb/>
               given &amp; received I trust<lb/>
               on this little occasion will<lb/>
               encourage you to indulge<lb/>
               yourself in future when<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_702_1843-03-30_page03.jpg"/>
               <note anchored="true">69</note>
            ever opportunity &amp; <choice>
                  <orig>tempta-<lb/>
                     tion</orig>
                  <reg instant="false">temptation</reg>
               </choice>
               well join for a <hi rend="underline">Spry</hi>
               (an American word acknow<lb/>
               (ledged by American dictionary<lb/>
               (which <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeH1" instant="false" full="yes">Harriet</persName> rich in Dic <hi rend="superscript">s</hi> possesses<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">I am so glad that<lb/>
               you had the luck at<lb/>
               the last moment to<lb/>
               catch the unpacking<lb/>
               of the picture of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#FoxW1" instant="false" full="yes">Walter</persName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
               though between you &amp;<lb/>
               I it is but a sorry drawing<lb/>
               and does not suit (in my<lb/>
               opinion the place where it<lb/>
               now is viz over the Bishop<lb/>
               of Meaths admirable head<lb/>
               and between you &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF2" instant="false" full="yes">Francis</persName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">I hope <persName ref="./Personography.xml#FoxM1" instant="false" full="yes">Mary Anne</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC2" instant="false" full="yes">Charlotte</persName>
               <lb/>
               will take it up to their own<lb/>
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_702_1843-03-30_page04.jpg"/> 
            
               room - It does not match any<lb/>
               thing in this room - &amp; I cant<lb/>
               abide it - But it was very good<lb/>
               of Aunt <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauH2" instant="false" full="yes">Henrietta</persName> to get it done<lb/>
               and to send it to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#FoxM1" instant="false" full="yes">Mary Anne</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC2" instant="false" full="yes">C</persName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
                A new music has just <choice>
                  <orig>ar-<lb/>
                     rived </orig>
                  <reg instant="false">arrived</reg>
               </choice>
               &amp; the room is all ears<lb/>
               And <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeL1" instant="false" full="yes">Lucy</persName> is judging - and<lb/>
               I am no judge but very<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               affectionately yours<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1" instant="false" full="yes">ME</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p part="N">
                  I am so glad you have <lb/>
                  Conde - Do you see in<lb/>
                  todays paper the report that<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StanP1" instant="false" full="yes">Lord Mahon</persName> is to go <choice>
                     <orig>Embassa<lb/>
                        dor</orig>
                     <reg instant="false">Embassador</reg>
                  </choice>
                  to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#SP" instant="false" full="yes">Spain</placeName> - I hope it is<lb/>
                  done - it would suit &amp;<lb/>
                  gratify him so much<lb/>
                  Thank you for mentioning<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SneyM1" instant="false" full="yes">Marys</persName> delight on her sealed<lb/>
                  packet - Love to all<lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
         </div>
